# Dependency Policy Rule

## The Rule

Every new **production dependency** must be listed and approved in [MANIFEST.md Section 10](../../MANIFEST.md#10-dependency-philosophy) before it can be added to any `package.json` in the `packages/` directory.

## Plugin Isolation Rule (Enforced Here)

**Plugins must not depend on each other.** Before adding any dependency to a plugin's `package.json`, verify:
- It is the `lastriko` core package (allowed), OR
- It is a third-party library specific to that plugin's domain (allowed), OR
- It is another `@lastriko/*` plugin package (NOT allowed — stop and raise this)

## Approved Production Dependencies

Currently approved (from MANIFEST.md Section 10.2):

| Package | Packages | Notes |
|---------|----------|-------|
| `nanostores` | `packages/core` | Server-side reactive state — non-replaceable |
| `ws` | `packages/core` | Node.js WebSocket fallback only — not needed on Bun |

**No CDN dependencies.** Lastriko ships its own `lastriko.css`. No Pico.css. No CDN links in `index.html`.

